trans-unit.source: Represents an *n*-tuple, where *n* is 8 or greater.
trans-unit.target: 表示 n 元组，n 为 8 或更大值。

trans-unit.source: A tuple is a data structure that has a specific number and sequence of values.
trans-unit.target: 元组是具有特定的数量和值序列的数据结构。

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Tuple%608> class represents an *n*-tuple that has eight or more components.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Tuple%608>类表示*n*元组具有八个或多个组件。

trans-unit.source: You can instantiate a <xref:System.Tuple%608> object with exactly eight components by calling the static <xref:System.Tuple.Create%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method.
trans-unit.target: 可以实例化<xref:System.Tuple%608>对象与通过调用静态完全八个组件<xref:System.Tuple.Create%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType>方法。

trans-unit.source: The following example creates an 8-tuple (octuple) that contains prime numbers that are less than 20.
trans-unit.target: 下面的示例创建一个 8 元组 （八元组） 包含小于 20 的质数。

trans-unit.source: Note that it uses type inference to determine the type of each component.
trans-unit.target: 请注意它使用类型推断功能来确定每个组件的类型。

trans-unit.source: You can also instantiate an n-tuple object with eight or more components by calling the <xref:System.Tuple%608.%23ctor%2A> constructor.
trans-unit.target: 你可以还通过实例化具有八个或多个组件的 n 元组对象调用<xref:System.Tuple%608.%23ctor%2A>构造函数。

trans-unit.source: The following example uses the <xref:System.Tuple%608.%23ctor%2A> constructor to create an 8-tuple that is equivalent to the tuple created in the previous example.
trans-unit.target: 下面的示例使用<xref:System.Tuple%608.%23ctor%2A>构造函数来创建的 8 元组，它等效于在前面的示例中创建元组。

trans-unit.source: To create an n-tuple with nine or more components, you must call the <xref:System.Tuple%608.%23ctor%2A> constructor.
trans-unit.target: 若要创建具有九个或多个组件的 n 元组，必须调用<xref:System.Tuple%608.%23ctor%2A>构造函数。

trans-unit.source: The static factory methods of the <xref:System.Tuple> class do not support the creation of `Tuple` objects with more than eight components.
trans-unit.target: 静态工厂方法的<xref:System.Tuple>类不支持创建`Tuple`包含多个八个组件的对象。

trans-unit.source: To instantiate an n-tuple that has eight or more components with the <xref:System.Tuple%608.%23ctor%2A> constructor, you supply a generic `Tuple` object as the `rest` parameter to define the eighth through *n*th components of the tuple.
trans-unit.target: 若要实例化 n 元组具有八个或多个组件<xref:System.Tuple%608.%23ctor%2A>构造函数，提供一个泛型`Tuple`对象作为`rest`参数定义的第八个通过*n*th 组件的元组。

trans-unit.source: By nesting generic `Tuple` objects in this way, you can create a tuple that has no practical limitation on the number of its components.
trans-unit.target: 通过嵌套泛型`Tuple`中这样一来，你可以创建其组件数有没有实际限制的元组的对象。

trans-unit.source: The following example creates a 17-tuple that contains population data for the city of Detroit, Michigan, for each national census from 1860 to 2000.
trans-unit.target: 下面的示例创建一个 17 元组包含填充数据的密歇根州底特律每个国家/地区人口普查从 1860年到 2000年。

trans-unit.source: The first component of the tuple is the city name.
trans-unit.target: 此元组的第一个组件是市/县名。

trans-unit.source: The second component is the start date of the data series, and the third component is the population at the start date.
trans-unit.target: 第二个部分是数据序列的开始日期和第三个组件是开始日期的人口。

trans-unit.source: Each subsequent component provides the population at decade intervals.
trans-unit.target: 每个后续组件提供十年间隔的人口。

trans-unit.source: The 17-tuple is created by nesting a <xref:System.Tuple%603> object inside a <xref:System.Tuple%608> object.
trans-unit.target: 17 元组创建的嵌套<xref:System.Tuple%603>对象内<xref:System.Tuple%608>对象。

trans-unit.source: (That is, the <xref:System.Tuple%603> object is supplied as the value of the `rest` parameter in the <xref:System.Tuple%608> class constructor.) This <xref:System.Tuple%608> object is, in turn, nested in an outer <xref:System.Tuple%608> object.
trans-unit.target: (这就是，则<xref:System.Tuple%603>对象提供的值作为`rest`中的参数<xref:System.Tuple%608>类构造函数。)这<xref:System.Tuple%608>对象，反过来，嵌套在为外部<xref:System.Tuple%608>对象。

trans-unit.source: (That is, the <xref:System.Tuple%608> object is supplied as the value of the `rest` parameter in the outer <xref:System.Tuple%608> object's class constructor.)
trans-unit.target: (这就是，则<xref:System.Tuple%608>对象提供的值作为`rest`中外部参数<xref:System.Tuple%608>对象的类构造函数。)

trans-unit.source: You can retrieve the value of the tuple's first seven components by using the read-only <xref:System.Tuple%607.Item1%2A>, <xref:System.Tuple%607.Item2%2A>, <xref:System.Tuple%607.Item3%2A>, <xref:System.Tuple%607.Item4%2A>, <xref:System.Tuple%607.Item5%2A>, <xref:System.Tuple%607.Item6%2A>, and <xref:System.Tuple%607.Item7%2A> instance properties.
trans-unit.target: 你可以通过使用只读的检索此元组的前七个组件的值<xref:System.Tuple%607.Item1%2A>， <xref:System.Tuple%607.Item2%2A>， <xref:System.Tuple%607.Item3%2A>， <xref:System.Tuple%607.Item4%2A>， <xref:System.Tuple%607.Item5%2A>， <xref:System.Tuple%607.Item6%2A>，和<xref:System.Tuple%607.Item7%2A>实例属性。

trans-unit.source: Any additional components are nested and can be retrieved from the <xref:System.Tuple%608.Rest%2A> property.
trans-unit.target: 任何其他组件嵌套的并且可以从检索<xref:System.Tuple%608.Rest%2A>属性。

trans-unit.source: In the previous example, the <xref:System.Tuple%608.Item1%2A> through <xref:System.Tuple%608.Item7%2A> properties retrieve the first through seventh components of the tuple.
trans-unit.target: 在前面的示例中，<xref:System.Tuple%608.Item1%2A>通过<xref:System.Tuple%608.Item7%2A>属性检索此元组的第七个组件之间的第一个。

trans-unit.source: The eighth through fourteenth components are contained in the tuple that is nested at the second level, and are represented by the `Rest.Item1` through `Rest.Item7` properties.
trans-unit.target: 通过第 14 个组件的第八个包含嵌套在第二个级别，该元组中，由表示`Rest.Item1`通过`Rest.Item7`属性。

trans-unit.source: The fifteenth through seventeenth components are contained in the tuple that is nested at the third level, and are represented by the `Rest.Rest.Item1` though `Rest.Rest.Item3` properties.
trans-unit.target: 第十五个到十七个组件包含在嵌套第三个级别的元组，并且由表示`Rest.Rest.Item1`尽管`Rest.Rest.Item3`属性。

trans-unit.source: Tuples are commonly used in four different ways:
trans-unit.target: 元组常用四个不同的方式：

trans-unit.source: To represent a single set of data.
trans-unit.target: 来表示一组数据。

trans-unit.source: For example, a tuple can represent a database record, and its components can represent individual fields of the record.
trans-unit.target: 例如，一个元组可以表示的数据库记录，并且其组件可以表示每个字段的记录。

trans-unit.source: To provide easy access to, and manipulation of, a data set.
trans-unit.target: 若要提供轻松访问和数据集的操作。

trans-unit.source: To return multiple values from a method without the use of `out` parameters (in C#) or `ByRef` parameters (in Visual Basic).
trans-unit.target: 若要通过无需使用方法返回多个值`out`参数 （在 C# 中) 或`ByRef`参数 （在 Visual Basic 中)。

trans-unit.source: For example, the previous example returns its computed statistics, along with the city name, in a <xref:System.Tuple%607> object.
trans-unit.target: 例如，前面的示例返回城市名称，其计算统计信息中<xref:System.Tuple%607>对象。

trans-unit.source: To pass multiple values to a method through a single parameter.
trans-unit.target: 若要将多个值传递给通过单个参数的方法。

trans-unit.source: For example, the <xref:System.Threading.Thread.Start%28System.Object%29?displayProperty=nameWithType> method has a single parameter that lets you supply one value to the method that the thread executes at startup.
trans-unit.target: 例如，<xref:System.Threading.Thread.Start%28System.Object%29?displayProperty=nameWithType>方法只有一个参数，你可以提供一个值，则在启动线程执行的方法。

trans-unit.source: If you supply a <xref:System.Tuple%607> object as the method argument, you can supply the thread’s startup routine with seven items of data.
trans-unit.target: 如果你提供<xref:System.Tuple%607>对象作为方法自变量，则可以提供具有七项数据的线程的启动例程。

trans-unit.target: 此元组的第一个组件的值。

trans-unit.source: When using the <xref:System.Tuple%608.%23ctor%2A> constructor to create an n-tuple with eight or more components, you use the `rest` parameter to create a nested n-tuple that has from one to seven components.

trans-unit.source: The following example creates a 17-tuple that contains population data for the city of Detroit, Michigan, for each census from 1860 to 2000.

trans-unit.source: Each subsequent component provides the population at decade intervals.

trans-unit.source: The example uses two layers of nesting to create the 17-tuple: It defines a 7-tuple whose third through seventh components contain population data for 1860 through 1900, a nested 7-tuple that contains population data for 1910 through 1970, and an inner nested 3-tuple that contains population data for 1980 through 2000.
trans-unit.target: 该示例使用嵌套的两个图层来创建 17 元组： 它定义的 7 元组的第三到第七个组件包含填充数据 1860 到 1900 年，嵌套 7 元组 1910 到 1970 年，包含填充数据和内部嵌套 3 元组包含从 1980 到 2000年填充数据。

trans-unit.source: Returns a value that indicates whether the current <see cref="T:System.Tuple`8" /> object is equal to a specified object.

trans-unit.source: The `obj` parameter is considered to be equal to the current instance if it meets all the following conditions:
trans-unit.target: `obj`参数被视为可与当前实例相等，如果它满足以下所有条件：

trans-unit.source: It is a <xref:System.Tuple%608> object.

trans-unit.source: It has the same total number of components that are of the same types as the current instance.
trans-unit.target: 它具有相同的类型与当前实例相同的组件的总数。

trans-unit.source: Its components (including its nested components) are equal to those of the current instance.
trans-unit.target: 其组件 （包括其嵌套的组件） 是等于当前实例。

trans-unit.source: Equality is determined by the default equality comparer for each component.
trans-unit.target: 相等性取决于每个组件的默认相等比较器。

trans-unit.source: Although this method can be called directly, it is most commonly called by collection-sorting methods that include <xref:System.Collections.IComparer> parameters to order the members of a collection.
trans-unit.target: 虽然可以直接调用此方法，它通常由集合排序方法包括<xref:System.Collections.IComparer>参数集合的成员进行排序。

trans-unit.source: For example, it is called by the <xref:System.Array.Sort%28System.Array%2CSystem.Collections.IComparer%29?displayProperty=nameWithType> method and the <xref:System.Collections.SortedList.Add%2A> method of a <xref:System.Collections.SortedList> object that is instantiated by using the <xref:System.Collections.SortedList.%23ctor%28System.Collections.IComparer%29?displayProperty=nameWithType> constructor.
trans-unit.target: 例如，它由<xref:System.Array.Sort%28System.Array%2CSystem.Collections.IComparer%29?displayProperty=nameWithType>方法和<xref:System.Collections.SortedList.Add%2A>方法<xref:System.Collections.SortedList>通过实例化的对象<xref:System.Collections.SortedList.%23ctor%28System.Collections.IComparer%29?displayProperty=nameWithType>构造函数。

trans-unit.source: The following example creates an array of <xref:System.Tuple%608> objects that contains population data for four U.S. cities from 1940 to 2000.
trans-unit.target: 下面的示例创建的数组<xref:System.Tuple%608>包含四个美国城市从 1940年到 2000年的填充数据的对象。

trans-unit.source: The octuple's first component is the city name.
trans-unit.target: 八元组的第一个组件是市/县名。

trans-unit.source: The remaining six components represent the population at 10-year intervals from 1940 to 2000.
trans-unit.target: 剩余的六个组件表示 1940年到 2000年 10 年间隔的人口。

trans-unit.source: The `PopulationComparer` class provides an <xref:System.Collections.IComparer> implementation that allows the array of octuples to be sorted by any one of its components.
trans-unit.target: `PopulationComparer`类提供<xref:System.Collections.IComparer>实现，它允许对八元及其组件的任何一个按排序数组。

trans-unit.source: Two values are provided to the `PopulationComparer` class in its constructor: The position of the component that defines the sort order, and a <xref:System.Boolean> value that indicates whether the tuple objects should be sorted in ascending or descending order.
trans-unit.target: 两个值提供给`PopulationComparer`其构造函数中的类： 定义排序顺序中，该组件的位置和一个<xref:System.Boolean>值，该值指示是否应按升序或降序排序元组对象。

trans-unit.source: The example then displays the elements in the array in unsorted order, sorts them by the third component (the population in 1950) and displays them, and then sorts them by the eighth component (the population in 2000) and displays them.
trans-unit.target: 该示例然后显示未排序顺序中的数组中的元素，按第三个组件 （1950 年的人口） 进行排序和显示，然后按第八个组件 （2000 年的人口） 进行排序并显示它们。

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Collections.IEqualityComparer.Equals%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> implementation is called only if `other` is not `null`, and if it can be successfully cast (in C#) or converted (in Visual Basic) to a <xref:System.Tuple%608> object that has the same total number of components (including those in nested `Tuple` objects) of the same types as the current instance.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEqualityComparer.Equals%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType>仅当调用实现`other`不`null`，和可以成功地强制转换 （在 C# 中) 或 （在 Visual Basic 中) 转换为<xref:System.Tuple%608>具有相同的总数量的组件的对象 （包括那些在嵌套`Tuple`对象) 的类型与当前实例相同。

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Tuple%608.System%23Collections%23IStructuralEquatable%23Equals%28System.Object%2CSystem.Collections.IEqualityComparer%29> method first passes the <xref:System.Tuple%608.Item1%2A> values of the <xref:System.Tuple%608> objects to be compared to the <xref:System.Collections.IEqualityComparer.Equals%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> implementation.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Tuple%608.System%23Collections%23IStructuralEquatable%23Equals%28System.Object%2CSystem.Collections.IEqualityComparer%29>方法第一个传递<xref:System.Tuple%608.Item1%2A>值<xref:System.Tuple%608>对象要进行比较<xref:System.Collections.IEqualityComparer.Equals%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType>实现。

trans-unit.source: If this method call returns `true`, the method is called again and passed the <xref:System.Tuple%608.Item2%2A> values of the two <xref:System.Tuple%608> objects.
trans-unit.target: 如果此方法调用返回`true`，再次调用该方法并将其传递<xref:System.Tuple%608.Item2%2A>这两个值<xref:System.Tuple%608>对象。

trans-unit.source: This continues until the method call returns `false` when it compares a specific pair of values, or the two <xref:System.Tuple%608.Rest%2A> values are passed to the method.

trans-unit.source: Although the method can be called directly, it is most commonly called by the default overloads of collection-sorting methods, such as <xref:System.Array.Sort%28System.Array%29?displayProperty=nameWithType> and <xref:System.Collections.SortedList.Add%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType>, to order the members of a collection.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Tuple%608.System%23IComparable%23CompareTo%2A> method is intended for use in sorting operations.

trans-unit.source: The string returned by this method takes the form (*Item1*, *Item2*, *Item3*, *Item4*, `Item5, Item6, Item7`, *Item8*…), where *Item1*, *Item2*, *Item3*, *Item4*, *Item5*, *Item6*, and *Item7* represent the values of the <xref:System.Tuple%608.Item1%2A>, <xref:System.Tuple%608.Item2%2A>, <xref:System.Tuple%608.Item3%2A>, <xref:System.Tuple%608.Item4%2A>, <xref:System.Tuple%608.Item5%2A>, <xref:System.Tuple%608.Item6%2A>, and <xref:System.Tuple%608.Item7%2A> properties.
trans-unit.target: 通过此方法返回的字符串的形式 (*Item1*， *Item2*， *Item3*， *Item4*， `Item5, Item6, Item7`， *Item8*...)，其中*Item1*， *Item2*， *Item3*， *Item4*， *Item5*， *Item6*，和*Item7*表示的值<xref:System.Tuple%608.Item1%2A>， <xref:System.Tuple%608.Item2%2A>， <xref:System.Tuple%608.Item3%2A>， <xref:System.Tuple%608.Item4%2A>， <xref:System.Tuple%608.Item5%2A>， <xref:System.Tuple%608.Item6%2A>，和<xref:System.Tuple%608.Item7%2A>属性。

trans-unit.source: *Item8* represents the value of the <xref:System.Tuple%608> object's `Next.Item1` property.
trans-unit.target: *Item8*表示的值<xref:System.Tuple%608>对象的`Next.Item1`属性。

trans-unit.source: The value of any additional nested components follow *Item8*.
trans-unit.target: 任何其他的嵌套组件的值遵循*Item8*。

trans-unit.target: 如果任何属性值为`null`，它会表示为<xref:System.String.Empty?displayProperty=nameWithType>。
